snippet.textDisplay: Thank you very much Professor Seheult! It's a very interesting and important question whether the vaccines can prevent "sufficient" infection ,(as far as I know most of the vaccines in general for other infectious diseases cannot prevent abortive infection) so to prevent transmission of the virus without causing illness in the "carrier", vaccinated person?
